definitions.definition: To reap grain, gather it up, and store it in a granary .
To gather , amass , hoard , as if harvesting grain.
To earn ; to get ; to accumulate or acquire by some effort or due to some fact
examples: He garnered a reputation as a language expert.
Her new book garnered high praise from the critics.
His poor choices garnered him a steady stream of welfare checks.

definitions.definition: To gather or become gathered; to accumulate or become accumulated; to become stored.

main_definition: To reap grain, gather it up, and store it in a granary .
secondary_definitions: To gather , amass , hoard , as if harvesting grain.
( often figurative ) To earn ; to get ; to accumulate or acquire by some effort or due to some fact
( rare ) To gather or become gathered; to accumulate or become accumulated; to become stored.
